Release:        1%{?dist}
Summary:        Cross-platform, multi-language runtime, package, and project manager
License:        MPL-2.0
URL:            https://github.com/BoxingOctopusCreative/linguo
Source0:        linguo-%{version}-vendored.tar.gz
BuildRequires:  cargo
BuildRequires:  rust
ExclusiveArch:  x86_64 aarch64

%description
linguo manages runtime versions, per-project pins, and project workflows
for Python, Node.js, Ruby, PHP, Rust, Go, Zig, the JVM stack (Java, Kotlin,
Groovy, Scala), and Terraform/OpenTofu with one uv-style command surface.
Toolchains are downloaded from each ecosystem's official source and
sha256-verified. The source tarball carries vendored cargo dependencies, so
the build runs offline.

%prep
%autosetup -n linguo-%{version}

%build
cargo build --release --offline

%install
install -Dm755 target/release/linguo %{buildroot}%{_bindir}/linguo

%files
%{_bindir}/linguo
%doc README.md
